"'''Little Girl'''" is a [[pop music|pop]] song written by Hubert Kemmler , Markus Lohr and [[Michael Cretu]] for [[Sandra (singer)|Sandra]]'s debut [[album]] ''[[The Long Play]]'' (1985). It was [[record producer|produced]] by [[Michael Cretu]], and received a mixed reception from music critics. The song was released as the third and final [[single (music)|single]] in the beginning of [[1986 in music|1986]] and was a top twenty hit in the [[Germany]] and [[Switzerland]], peaking at number fourteen and eighteen, respectively.<ref>[http://lescharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Sandra&titel=Little+Girl&cat=s lescharts.com]</ref>

==Formats and track listings==
'''7" single'''
#"Little Girl" - 3:11
#"[[The Long Play#Sisters and Brothers|Sisters and Brothers]]" - 3:23

'''12" single'''
#"Little Girl" (extended mix) - 5:09
#"[[The Long Play#Sisters and Brothers|Sisters and Brothers]]" - 3:23

==Music video==
The music video was directed by Mike Stiebel and filmed in Venice in early [[1986]]. It shows Sandra walking through the streets and looking for a little girl.

